> I was wondering how to have a logo that is in some sort of script style 
> lettering write itself in an animation.

 Render out a single image o the entire logo you 
wish to have written on.  Save it as an alpha channel image.  Load it in 
to ADPRO make it a 2 color image.  Load the image into Dpaint and creat 
animation frames for it. When you have the logo writing on the way you 
like it in a 2D animation, save off all the frames as an image sequence.
Go back to lightwave load the image sequence.  Then load your logo 
object.  Goto the object menu and use your sequence as a clip map for 
that object.  You'll have to play with the image map sizing till ya get 
it scaled right, and wala you now have writing text without morphing.

