 Here is a technique:
for single trees, ones that will not be close by, take an image of a tree and
apply it as an image map and have the background of that image be a transparency
map. Take two of these polygons and stick them into each other at a right angle.
from any view (except above) this should look like a tree from a distance.
If you want an above view to work, make a third polygon with a view of the
top of the tree.

For more complex trees, path extrude a cross-section of some kind and build
the trunk however you wish.  For branches, use the same technique for the 
other tree style except use it for the branches.  You may wish to put the
mapping on four or five polygons and bend it for a curvature.  I have had some
successful results doing this.
-joe Solinsky
